<HEADLINE>
INTERNET SITE OF THE WEEK
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DAVID BLOOM 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Icebox: A just-launched site for often funny, if foul-mouthed,
original animation series. &QL; 
Where: www.icebox.com &QL; 
What's cool: Icebox is competing with a rash of Web-based
entertainment sites _ including other newcomers such as iFuse.com,
The Romp, Synge.com and Thirsty.com _ trying to attract audiences
and attention. It has one potential advantage over most of the
competition: writers such as ``Seinfeld'' co-creator Larry David
and other top-notch talent formerly associated with notable shows
such as ``The Simpsons,'' ``Futurama,'' ``Frasier'' and many more. &QL; 
Features: ``Zombie College'' has gotten the most attention, a funny
if sometimes crude take on life in a very strange sort of
institution of higher learning. ``Hard Drinkin' Lincoln'' is a
profane (in many ways) but funny take on one of our most important
presidents; then again, if you were married to crazy Mary Todd and
simultaneously had to preserve the Union, you'd make like Ulysses
S. Grant and kill off a bottle of whiskey a day, too. &QL; 
You'll like this if: You want to see what all the good writers are
doing during summer rerun season. Goodness knows, you won't want to
watch much TV.
</P>
</TEXT>
