<P>
   RUSSIA-ARREST (Moscow) _ Russian prosecutors on Friday filed
charges of large-scale fraud against Vladimir Gusinsky, the owner
of Russia's leading independent media conglomerate. By Celestine
Bohlen.
</P>
<P>
   GERMANY-RUSSIA (Berlin) _ A Russian-German summit meeting that
ended Friday produced a vigorous rapprochement of the two
countries. The meeting led to agreements on German investments in
Russia worth $1.7 billion, cautious German backing of a plan for
Russia to involve itself in the defense of Europe against missile
attack, and the establishment of an apparently excellent rapport
between Vladimir Putin and Gerhard Schroeder. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
