   SKOREA-NKOREA (Seoul, South Korea) _ Following the three-day
summit meeting between the leaders of North and South Korea, both
nations ended propaganda broadcasts against each other and families
rushed to sign up for reunions. By Calvin Sims.
</P>
<P>
   AFRICA-DRUG-PRICES (Nairobi, Kenya) _ The prices of life-saving
medicines in Africa, where the need is greatest and the poverty is
worst, are often higher than those in Europe and North America,
according to a study released here Friday. By Donald G. McNeil Jr.
</P>
<P>
   U.N.-CONGO (United Nations) _ Developments in discussions on the
conflict in Congo with ministers from a half dozen African nations.
By Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
<P>
   OBIT-NAGAKO (Undated) _ Dowager Empress Nagako of Japan, the
97-year-old widow of Emperor Hirohito, died Friday after a life
that spanned the transformation of her homeland several times over.
Nagako spent her life insulated deep inside a Japan that no longer
exists. Indeed, she was one of the last Japanese who could remember
life inside the aristocracy early in the 20th century or in the
palace during the time when people spoke an archaic, imperial form
of Japanese that has largely disappeared. By Nicholas D. Kristof.
</P>
