a just a chance to win a trip to Australia, they're a huge fork in
the road. (Maher, Austin American-Statesman). 31.
</P>
<P>
   DIV-OLY-CULPEPPER _ Ashley Culpepper may still not be able to
remember it, but she did have at least one bad day this year. It
came on May 11, when the former Westwood diver was warming up for
the three-meter springboard competition at the FINA/USA Diving
Grand Prix at Ft. Lauderdale. She came down too close to the board
and slammed her head against it, opening a deep gash that required
two staples to close. She suffered a concussion and not only had to
withdraw from the international meet, she had to be hospitalized.
(Maher, Austin American-Statesman). 20.
