<SLUG> BC-SPRINT-STREET </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SPRINT PCS PRESIDENT RESIGNS 
</HEADLINE>
   (EDS: Stock prices in this story are not up to the moment.)  
 By SARAH RUBENSTEIN   
 c.2000 NYTimes.com/TheStreet.com   
<TEXT>
<P>
   (For use by clients of The New York Times News Service)
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Sprint PCS announced Friday that Andrew Sukawaty was
stepping down as president and chief operating officer.
</P>
<P>
   The wireless telephone company said Sukawaty, 44, was leaving to
pursue ``a new opportunity,'' but it did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
   His resignation was unexpected, Tom Murphy, a Sprint PCS
spokesman, said. Murphy said the company did not yet have a
replacement for Sukawaty.
</P>
<P>
   Ronald T. LeMay, president and chief operating officer of the
wireless company's parent, Sprint, will replace Sukawaty for an
interim period, Murphy said. Sukawaty will act as a consultant to
LeMay during the next month.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Sprint PCS were trading down 1 1/2, or 2 percent, at
60 15/16 around midday Friday. Sprint's stock was flat at 58 9/16.
</P>
<P>
   Sukawaty said in a statement that his decision to leave the
fourth start-up venture in which he has been involved had been a
difficult one. He said he would provide more information about his
next position at a later date. The departure comes as the
long-distance company WorldCom is trying to get regulatory approval
to buy Sprint.
</P>
<P>
   Sukawaty joined Sprint PCS as chief executive officer in 1996
and became president and chief operating officer in December 1998
when Sprint acquired financial and management control of the joint
venture between Sprint, TeleCommunications, Comcast and Cox
Communications.
</P>
<P>
   LeMay was chief executive of Sprint Spectrum from 1995 to 1996
before the company became Sprint PCS.
</P>
<P>
   In a statement LeMay said of Sukawaty that Sprint PCS ``has
grown from a few thousand customers to 7 million and has become the
fastest-growing wireless personal communications services provider
in United States history. That is testimony to his contribution.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-06-16-00 1456EDT &QL; 
