<HEADER>
A6019 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-SUMMER-TV0617-COX     06-16 0938
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUMMER-TV0617-COX </SLUG>

<TEXT>
<P>
   Summer TV lineupc. 2000 Cox News Service
</P>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio - ``Totally Circus''
</P>
<P>
   Starts today, (Disney Channel, 4 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A documentary/adventure series that offers an
up-close-and-personal look at young circus performers. Get a load
of those grueling rehearsals and stress-relieving pillow fights!
Think ``Making the Band''_ kiddie style.
</P>
<P>
   Will it fizzle or sizzle? We all know how miserably ``Making the
Band'' tanked.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 1 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``The League of Gentlemen''
</P>
<P>
   Starts Monday,
</P>
<P>
   (Comedy Central, 10:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A zany British sketch comedy in the mold of
``Saturday Night Live'' and ``The Benny Hill Show.''
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Can anyone really top Benny Hill?
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't Forget Your Toothbrush''
</P>
<P>
   Starts Tuesday,
</P>
<P>
   (Comedy Central, 10 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A goofy game show in which contestants are
asked to take part in humiliating challenges for trips to such
places as London and Scotland. The catch? They're whisked away on
the spot. Mark Curry (''Hangin' with Mr. Cooper'') hosts.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Don't expect a ``Who Wants To Be A
Millionaire''-like hit, but there's something to be said for a game
show that has the nerve to ask a blindfolded female contestant to
identify what's hanging underneath a man's kilt. I'm not kidding.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 3 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Resurrection Blvd.''
</P>
<P>
   Starts June 26, (Showtime, 10 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A proud Latino family of fighters strives to
achieve the American Dream despite heartaches and tragedy.
</P>
<P>
   Will it fizzle or sizzle? ``Resurrection Blvd.'' deserves to be
TV's next great cable series. A top-notch cast led by ``New York
Undercover''''s Michael DeLorenzo and engaging storytelling makes
this compelling series a must-see. As a UCLA pre-med
student-turned-amateur boxer, look for Nicholas Gonzalez to become
TV's version of Ricky Martin.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 4 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Opposite Sex''
</P>
<P>
   Starts June 28,
</P>
<P>
   (WFLX-Channel 29, 8 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A lighthearted, coming-of-age drama about a
15-year-old who's one of only three male students at a formerly
all-girl prep school.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? ``Opposite Sex'' comes from the
creators of the hit film ``Never Been Kissed.'' That was a funny
movie. So that means. . . nothing.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Style World''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 10 (Romance Classics, 8 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Host Rachel Hunter takes viewers on a virtual
trip to such far-away places as London, Venice and Stockholm to
explore each country's unique style and design. Viewers spy
everything from the chic interior of a city penthouse to the rustic
charm of a country cottage
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? The va-va-voomy Hunter and lush
locales? What's not to like? The problem: Who watches Romance
Classics?
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 2 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Young Americans''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 12, (WB, 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Good-looking kids from different backgrounds
try to get along at a New England boarding school.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? This derivative drama should fade
faster than bluejeans in a tub full of bleach.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 1 sun
</P>
<P>
   ``Don't Quote Me''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 17, (VH1, 10:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A tongue-in-cheek music video series in the
``Pop Up Video'' mold. Words from and about the artists are
superimposed while the videos play. Expect fun to be poked at
Cher's plastic surgery, Elton John's drama queen attitude and
Jennifer Lopez's legendary posterior.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Hey, we like making fun of Lopez's
rear, too. ``Don't Quote Me'' should amuse and delight. But don't
expect it to last much longer than your average music video.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 3 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Sound Affects''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 21, (VH1, 10 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? People talk about how songs inspired or
affected them in profound and powerful ways.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? No lurid drug overdoses? Backstage
fighting? Teary-eyed reunions? Awww, who cares?
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 1 sun
</P>
<P>
   ``Sammy''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 25, (WPTV-Channel 5, 8:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? An animated comedy that's loosely based on
David Spade's unusual relationship with his absentee, philandering
father.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? ``Sammy'' has great comedic voice
talents in Spade, Andy Dick (''NewsRadio'') and Janeane Garofalo
(''The Larry Sanders Show''), but if NBC had high hopes for the
series, it wouldn't have dumped it in that network TV graveyard
called July.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 1 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Courage''
</P>
<P>
   Starts Aug. 7,
</P>
<P>
   (Fox Family Channel, 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Danny Glover hosts this reality series which
profiles people who have displayed extraordinary courage. Among
those featured are an 11-year-old boy with a rare leg disease who
is now a champion swimmer and a 66-year-old crossing guard who
threw herself in front of a speeding truck to save the lives to two
children.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Inspirational stories. The commanding
Glover. Sounds like a sure bet.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 3 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``VH1 Confidential''
</P>
<P>
   Starts Aug. 14, (VH1, 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? A one-hour series that boasts it'll unearth the
mysteries, myths and urban legends of rock 'n' roll. Like? Well,
VH1 ain't sayin'.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Isn't ``Behind The Music'' enough?
Could be too much of a good thing.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 2 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
