<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-16 16:31 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6028 &Cx1f; tad-z
u e BC-SUMMER-TV-SIDE0617-CO     06-16 0518
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SUMMER-TV-SIDE0617-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Summer TV shows worth a look
 &HT;    By Kevin D. Thompson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _
</P>
<P>
   ``Strip Mall''
</P>
<P>
   Starts Sunday,
</P>
<P>
   (Comedy Central, 10:30 p.m)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Lust! Greed! Porn! That about sums up what goes
on in a seedy San Fernando Valley strip mall and in this
delightfully dopey soap satire. Julie Brown (''Earth Girls Are
Easy'') stars as Tammi Tyler, a daffy former child star (she knifed
her Captain Kangaroo-like co-star to death after eating a cupcake
laced with PCP) who now works as a barmaid at a tacky bar. The
sight gags should make you scream. See an X-rated ``Titanic'' See a
still loopy Victoria Jackson! See a woman make love. . . to a taco!
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Crude, crass, sexist and scathingly
funny. Could be Comedy Central's next ``South Park''-like hit.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 4 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Soul Food''
</P>
<P>
   Starts June 28,
</P>
<P>
   (Showtime, 10 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? If you saw the hit 1997 movie, you have a good
idea. The series follows the struggles and triumphs of a close-knit
black family in Chicago. You know, stuff like sick babies, house
leaks, nasty lawsuits, taboo romances. Oh, yeah, they also eat a
lot. And in ``Sex and the City'' fashion, they have a lot of sex,
too. Out are such big-name stars as Vivica A. Fox, Vanessa L.
Williams and Nia Long. In are such low-rent actors as Nicole Ari
Parker, Malinda Williams and the other Vanessa Williams _ the one
from ``Beverly Hills 90210.''
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Hey, the film grossed an impressive
$43 million. I'd bet a month's paycheck that many of those same
people get Showtime. Black audiences should make this show a hit.
It's certainly several notches better than the dreadfully dull
``Linc's.''
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 3 1/2 suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Big Brother''
</P>
<P>
   Starts July 5 (WPEC-Channel 12, 9 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Ten people who never met live together for 100
days in an 1,800-square-foot house rigged with 24 cameras, 60
microphones and, let's hope, zero rats.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? Unfortunately, viewers' appetite for
in-your-face reality TV appears insatiable. ``Big Brother'' should
satisfy that ever-growing hunger. But something tells me this isn't
what George Orwell had in mind when he wrote ``1984.''
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: Four suns
</P>
<P>
   ``Spy Groove''
</P>
<P>
   Starts June 26,
</P>
<P>
   (MTV, 10:30 p.m.)
</P>
<P>
   What's it about? Two super-cool, designer-clad secret agents
travel the globe to rid the world of stylish villains, fashionable
impostors and vanity junkies. In other words, they fight bad style.
They prowl such hot spots as Miami Beach and Beverly Hills in a
lime green (!) convertible that sports ``We R Spies'' tags. The
``Dr. No''-type bad guys include Mr. Fish, who looks like a badly
drawn Don Knotts, and some guy named Rock Debris.
</P>
<P>
   Will it sizzle or fizzle? A visually arresting animated series
(bold technicolors, rapidly changing backdrops), but lacks true
comic punch.
</P>
<P>
   Our buzz rating: 2 suns
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
