<P>
   USCAN-MAIN_ ATLANTA _ Robert Sunday never imagined he'd be a
grocery check-out clerk. But he gladly does the job for free at his
neighborhood Kroger. Sunday, 29, uses the express self check-out
line, where he scans and bags his own groceries, then feeds money
into a machine. ``I've used it ever since the service started,''
Sunday said during a recent shopping run. The machines, called
U-Scan Express, have been limited to lines for shoppers checking
out 15 items or less, and only some stores have them. But they are
showing up in growing numbers as Kroger and other retailers use
self checkout technology to solve labor shortages and cut costs.
There are questions as to how far the trend can go, such as whether
people are competent enough to do this without creating logjams.
(DeGross, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 24.
</P>
<P>
   WITH
</P>
<P>
   USCAN-FIRSTPERSON_ ATLANTA _ From now on I'm only picking the
Vidalia onions with coded stickers. That's one of the lessons I
learned during my first encounter with a Kroger U-Scan at the
chain's Monroe Drive store. Our retail reporter confronts her first
U-Scan machine and lives to tell about it. (DeGross, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   APPLIANCES _ Consumers may be cutting back on some spending, but
apparently they're still snapping up expensive appliances. General
Electric has ramped up production at a plant in Lafayette to meet
demand for its new high-end Spectra range. Home Depot's entry into
appliance sales has sparked some of the demand. GE added 150 jobs
and $5 million to support a third assembly line. Checking with
Maytag to find out how production is being affected by Home Depot.
(Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
</P>
<P>
   FLOORING-AMERICA _ ATLANTA _ Follow-up on Flooring America,
which filed for Chap. 11 Thursday. Interview with new chairman
David Nichols, who will talk about where the company will go from
here. (Bond, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-ACURA _ A review of the Acura 3.2CL Type S. (DeVault,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 10.
