   COXNET BUDGET INFORMATION FOR SUBSCRIBERS OF THE NYT NEWS
SERVICE
</P>
<P>
   Spot news budgets move daily at 2 p.m. and 6 p.m. Eastern.
Additionally, separate features and commentary budgets move at 10
a.m., and sports and business budgets at 6 p.m. Additional updates
are possible if news developments warrant.
</P>
<P>
   All times are Eastern unless otherwise noted. If stories will
move after 9:30 p.m., an ETA will be given.
</P>
<P>
   PHOTOS, LAYOUTS and GRAPHICS CoxNet layouts are for sale over
the web, through the New York Times News Service's PageExpress
service, at http://nytsyn.com/syndicate/pageex.
</P>
<P>
   If a budget line or story is marked with photos or graphics,
those are available from the New York Times News Service at
212-556-4204. Or call CoxNet for more information at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   HOW TO REACH US
</P>
<P>
   Questions should be directed to CoxNet, the Cox News Service, in
Atlanta at 404-526-5456. We are staffed 8 a.m. to 10 p.m.
Monday-Friday, and 1-10 p.m. on weekends and holidays.
</P>
<P>
   The day news editor is Tom Oder, 404-526-5887,
toder(at)coxnews.com.
</P>
<P>
   The nigh
</P>
<P>
   With its lengthy list of standard features _ including an
in-dash six-disc CD player, power everything and leather trim _ the
Type S shows that Honda is very serious about upgrading the Acura's
image. And its horsepower and torque numbers, along with a
zero-to-60 mph time of 6.6 seconds, indicate that the performance
is there, too.
</P>
<P>
   It's no fun getting in and out of the headroom-impaired rear
seat, but the ride, road-holding characteristics and soundproofing
of the Type S are all commendable. Fuel mileage is about what's
expected of V-6 engines with muscle, 19 mpg in the city and 29 mpg
on the highway, and so is the fuel recommendation (premium).
</P>
<P>
   The interior and instrumentation layout show both thought and
good workmanship. The far-reaching Xenon headlamps may aggravate
oncoming drivers, but they're a plus for whoever's behind the wheel
of the Type S (and other CLs).
</P>
<P>
   So never mind that the styling isn't as edgy or as appealing as
the mechanicals and creature comforts of Type S. Its performance
and utility _ yes, that too _ suggest that compared to some cars in
its class, it's a bargain.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
