(IFE), Mexico's answer to electoral corruption, has three weeks to
convince voters here and those elsewhere that this historic
presidential election will be fair. But with the long-ruling
Institutional Revolutionary Party at risk of finally losing the
presidency, concerns are growing _ among international observers
such as the Atlanta-based Carter Center and Mexican elections
officials _ that the PRI may not be willing to go quietly.
Developing. (Ferriss, Cox News Service). 40. WITH PHOTO.
