<P>
   NETHAWAY-COLUMN _ WACO, Texas _ Americans spend billions of
dollars each year trying to lose weight. The bloated federal
government has announced an expensive new effort to crack down on
the proliferation of diet doctors and weight-loss outfits that
promise quick and easy weight loss. With all this money being
thrown around in search of an effective way to lose weight and keep
it off, I felt the time was right to offer the public my sure-fire
weight-loss program. (Rowland Nethaway is senior editor of the Waco
Tribune-Herald) MOVEDMINTER-COLUMN _ The newspaper business 50
years ago had not progressed much past the horse and buggy. In the
newsroom, rows of teletype machines brought news in from wires
strung all over the world. (MINTER, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
MOVEDMCCARTY-COLUMN _ We all feel outrage when police officers are
second-guessed, even in clear-cut, self-defense cases. We all know
that police must make split-second, life-and-death decisions. Yet,
the controversial Bruce Springsteen song is hardly an Ice-T-style,
anti-police diatribe. It recognizes those complexities in a chorus
that repeats the thoughts that might have run through the officers'
minds. (MCCARTY, DAYTON DAILY NEWS) MOVED
</P>
