   RELIGION
</P>
<P>
   RELIGION-FATHERS _ He's just a guy one day; the next day, he's a
father. It's a miraculous transformation through birth or adoption
that changes a man's identity and outlook forever. We look at the
spiritual dimensions of fatherhood through fathers, and through the
eyes of doctors and nurses who have witnessed families being made.
(GWhite, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35. WITH PHOTOS and LAYOUT.
</P>
<P>
   BAPTISTS-MERRITT _ Everybody's somebody in Snellville, as the
saying goes, but the Rev. James Merritt , pastor of Snellville
First Baptist Church is now somebody all across the 15.8 million
member Southern Baptist Convention. Merritt is expected to be
elected Tuesday to head the body for at least the next year. He
follows in the footsteps of Atlantans Charles Stanley and Bailey
Smith in a line of conservative leaders who stretch back two
decades. But Merritt marks a generational change. He's the first
Baby Boomer president of the convention. (Gwhite, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
