<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times has added this breaking story,
LOS-ALAMOS-DATA, to its national report.
</P>
<P>
   LOS-ALAMOS-DATA (Washington) _ Missing computer hard drives from
Los Alamos National Laboratory containing nuclear secrets have been
found, officials said Friday afternoon. The two hard drives,
containing nuclear weapons data used by the government's Nuclear
Emergency Search Team, were found behind a duplicating machine,
according to one knowledgeable official. But while the
circumstances of the loss and discovery seemed, on the surface, to
be mundane rather than high-drama espionage, no one who has
followed the episode was drawing conclusions Friday afternoon. By
James Risen.
</P>
