<P>
   DEATH-PENALTY (Undated) _ About 200 cases have been prosecuted
under a federal law that allows death sentences for perpetrators of
murders connected to drug dealing, robberies, carjackings,
terrorism and abductions. But only about 23 have resulted in death
sentences, and 13 are either on appeal, were reversed, or are being
retried or resentenced. By Cindy Rodriguez. 1000 words.
