Massachusetts was the biggest on record in the Connecticut River
Valley. But earthquakes of similar size occur somewhere in New
England 2 or 3 times a year. In fact, New England, which is a
geological patchwork, could face a magnitude 6 or greater quake at
some point. By David L. Chandler. 1000 words.
