<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following business
story for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Saturday, June 17, and thereafter. For questions about stories,
contact Michael McGarr at the Daily News, (818) 713-3470.
</P>
<P>
   RECYCLING-CENTERS (Los Angeles) _ Tomra Inc., the company that
operates the grungy trailers often found tucked away behind grocery
stores, is going for a cleaner, more environmentally friendly
image. And they're moving to the front of the store with rePlanet,
a new species of recycling centers that have begun to appear at
Southern California grocery stores in advance of a national
roll-out. By Jason Z. Cohen.
</P>
