   BELLATLANTIC-GTE (Washington) _ The Federal Communications
Commission on Friday approved the merger of Bell Atlantic and GTE,
clearing the final obstacle to the creation of the nation's largest
telephone company. The new company, which will be called Verizon,
will control a third of the nation's local telephone lines on top
of 25 million cell phone customers. The FCC laid down 25 conditions
for approval, designed to promote competition and enhance local
phone competition. By Stephen Labaton.
