the United States. Frankel, arrested in Germany in September after
evading the FBI for months, pleaded guilty Friday to German charges
that he evaded taxes on about $5 million worth of diamonds he had
brought to Europe to finance his flight from the United States.
Friday's plea removes the main obstacle to Frankel's extradition to
the United States, where he faces more than 30 charges of fraud and
money laundering, as well as civil suits claiming damages of $600
million. By Edmund L. Andrews.
