<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   DEATH-PENALTY (Undated) _ About 200 cases have been prosecuted
under a federal law that allows death sentences for perpetrators of
murders connected to drug dealing, robberies, carjackings,
terrorism and abductions. But only about 23 have resulted in death
sentences, and 13 are either on appeal, were reversed, or are being
retried or resentenced. By Cindy Rodriguez. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   NY-TOURISM (New York) _ The Big Apple has become concerned that
tourism could be hurt by the bad publicity stemming from the
Central Park melee last weekend. Security in the park is stepped
up. 900 words.
</P>
<P>
   MASS-QUAKE (Weston, Mass.) _ A 3.3 magnitude quake in western
Massachusetts was the biggest on record in the Connecticut River
Valley. But earthquakes of similar size occur somewhere in New
England 2 or 3 times a year. In fact, New England, which is a
geological patchwork, could face a magnitude 6 or greater quake at
some point. By David L. Chandler. 1000 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FINANCIAL (f) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   HARVARD-STARTUPS (Undated) _ Harvard's Kennedy School takes a
tougher line than most professional schools on faculty involvement
in student start-ups. A new policy prohibits professors from active
participation in such ventures until three months after students
graduate, and bars informal discussions beforehand. By Ross Kerber.
900 words.
</P>
<P>
   FRAMINGHAM-HEART (Boston) _ Medical ethicists warn that Boston
University is wandering into ethically challenging geography with
its plans to sell data derived from the famous heart study of
10,000 Framingham, Mass. residents. By Liz Kowalczyk. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   CAISSE-NVEST (Boston) _ Caisse des Depots et Consignations, the
owner of France's second-largest money management company, acquires
Nvest LP for $2.2 billion in cash and debt. By Kathryn Tong. 600
words.
</P>
<P>
   TKT-FABRYS (Undated) _ Transkaryotic Therapies begins process to
gain approval for a drug to treat Fabry's disease, a rare genetic
disorder, beating Genzyme in the race for Orphan Drug Act
designation _ the right to exclusive marketing of their drug
without competition for seven years. By Ronald Rosenberg. 500
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; SPORTS (s) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   BBA-SOSA (Chicago) _ Slugger Sammy Sosa is annoyed that his
friend, Manny Alexander, is saying Sosa would like to be traded. By
Gordon Edes. 1500 words.
