<HEADLINE>
ACCORD ON MONITORING VOTE  

</HEADLINE>
   c.2000 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MEXICO CITY _ The two leading opposition candidates for the
presidency, Vicente Fox Quesada and Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, joined
Friday in a pact to defend the balloting on July 2 against fraud.
They agreed that their parties would work together to monitor the
voting and report vote buying. The accord included a minor
candidate, Manuel Camacho Solis.
</P>
</TEXT>
