   (NYT24) SAN FRANCISCO -- June 16, 2000 -- ADV. FOR SUN. JUNE 18
-- INVEST-MONTGOMERY -- Oscar A. Castro, 45, manager of the $590
million Montgomery Global Communications fund. Global
Communications has returned 47.2 percent a year, on average, for
the three years through June 9, versus 43.3 percent for its peers,
according to Morningstar Inc. Castro attributes his fund's
performance to its research process. While many analysts and money
managers focus on information gleaned from corporate management,
the Montgomery analysts pay special attention to company rivals,
suppliers and industry regulators. Castro playing tennis at San
Francisco's Golden Gate Tennis Club. (Thor Swift/The New York
Times)
