having set up it's own telecommunications company. The city's
expanding telecommunications net has persuaded Enterprise Corp.
International, a Des Moines-based company that offers technical
support and software for Sony and other electronics manufacturers,
to double its current staff of 28 in town. (Kent Sievers/The New
York Times)
