division and a move to upstate New York, Corning is still making
plenty of glass products in Massachusetts -- but a thousand times
smaller, and a million times more profitable. Technicians Lucy Dias
and Leo Lord test a laser chip at Corning Lasertron's plant.
Lasertron is one of several firms added to Corning's stable in the
last 18 months. (Tom Landers/The Boston Globe)
