the biggest issue facing Bashar Assad is how he will handle peace
talks his father, Hafez Assad, started but never finished. His
fellow Syrians have set a high standard that could be summed up as,
``Stay firm, or else.'' Imam Ghassan Hamdam presides over the
Na'issa Mosque in Qardaha, Syria, Hafez Assad's hometown, named
after the late president's mother. (Larry Kaplow/Cox News Service)
